public abstract class NCLParam<T extends NCLElement,Ec extends NCLConnectorParam,R extends ExternalReferenceType>
extends NCLElementPrototype<T>
implements NCLElement<T>

Class that represents a link or bind parameter element. This element is used to define a value to a parameter defined in a connector.
This element defines the attributes:

  • name - reference to the name of the parameter defined by a connector. This attribute is required.
  • value - value of the parameter defined by a connector. This attribute is required.

setName

public void setName(Ec connectorParam)
             throws XMLException
Sets the reference to the name of the parameter defined by the connector. This attribute is required and can not be set to null.
The connector parameter referred must be a parameter defined by the connector used by the link where this parameter element is defined.

Parameters:

XMLException - if the connector parameter is null or any error occur while creating the reference to the connector parameter.
